dcterms:description: Dblp is a co-authorship network where each node is an author and two authors are connected by an edge if they have co-authored a paper. The label of a node is the venue where the authors has published most frequently.
dcterms:title: Dblp

dcterms:creator: Jure Leskovec
Rok Sosiˇc
dcterms:description: Each node in Amazon represents a product and two nodes are connected by an edge if they are frequently co-purchased. The graph is unlabeled and hence equivalent to a graph containing a single label on all nodes.
dcterms:title: Amazon

dcterms:creator: Aleksandar Bojchevski
Stephan Günnemann
dcterms:description: PubMed dataset is a citation network which consists of scientific publications from PubMed database pertaining to diabetes classified into one of three classes.
dcterms:title: PubMed

dcterms:creator: Angela Bonifati
Wim Martens
Thomas Timm
dcterms:description: CiteSeer is a citation network which consists of scientific publications classified into one of six classes. Generally a smaller version is used for this dataset, but we use the larger version.
dcterms:title: CiteSeer

dcterms:creator: Aleksandar Bojchevski
Stephan Günnemann
dcterms:description: Cora dataset is a citation dataset consisting of many scientific publications classified into one of seven classes based on paper topic. Cora_ML is a smaller dataset extracted from Cora.
dcterms:title: Cora_ML

dcterms:description: Protein dataset consists of protein graphs. Each node is labeled with a one of three functional roles of the protein.
dcterms:title: Protein

dcterms:description: AIDS dataset consists of graphs constructed from the AIDS antiviral screen database. These graphs representing molecular compounds with Hydrogen atoms omitted. Atoms are represented as nodes and chemical bonds as edges.
dcterms:title: AIDS

dcterms:description: AIDS’ dataset is another collection of graphs constructed from the AIDS antiviral screen database. The graphs and their properties differ from those in AIDS. These graphs also represent chemical compound structures.
dcterms:title: AIDS’

dcterms:description: Linux dataset is a collection of program dependence graphs, where each graph is a function and nodes represent statements while edges represent dependency between statements.
dcterms:title: Linux

dcterms:description: IMDB dataset is a collection of ego-networks of actors/actresses that have appeared together in any movie.
dcterms:title: IMDB
